<title>USA: AES to sell $400-$450 mln of securities.</title>
<headline>AES to sell $400-$450 mln of securities.</headline>
<dateline>ARLINGTON, Va. 1997-03-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>AES Corp on Wednesday said it planned to sell common stock and convertible securities with an expected aggregate value of about $400 million to $450 million under its existing shelf registration.</p>
<p>The global power company said it would use the proceeds to repay debt and fund the previously announced acquisition of the international business of Destec Energy Inc.</p>
<p>The underwriting group, led by J.P. Morgan &amp; Co, plans to market the securities in the United States and other countries, AES said.</p>
<p>((New York newsdesk 212-859-1610))</p>
